The absence of the combed edge on the fore tibial spur is a peculiarity which ocuurs elsewhere within the tribe only in 
<emphasis box="[706,776,1526,1547]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1829">Iswara</emphasis>
WESTWOOD 1851 males; its outline is as the same as in 
<emphasis box="[482,618,1556,1578]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1829">Poecilotiphia</emphasis>
CAMERON 1902 males. Flagellum, hair and genitalia are like in 
<emphasis box="[382,443,1587,1608]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1829">Meria</emphasis>
